    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="JER 5:1" />Run ye to and <char style="w" strong="H7751">fro</char> through the <char style="w" strong="H2351">streets</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3389">Jerusalem</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H7200">see</char> now, and <char style="w" strong="H3045">know</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H1245">seek</char> in the broad <char style="w" strong="H7339">places</char> thereof, if ye can <char style="w" strong="H4672">find</char> a <char style="w" strong="H0376">man</char>, if there <char style="w" strong="H3426">be</char> <char style="add">any</char> that <char style="w" strong="H6213">executeth</char> <char style="w" strong="H4941">judgment</char>, that <char style="w" strong="H1245">seeketh</char> the <char style="w" strong="H0530">truth</char>; and I will <char style="w" strong="H5545">pardon</char> it. <verse eid="JER 5:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="JER 5:2" />And though they <char style="w" strong="H0559">say</char>, The <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> <char style="w" strong="H2416">liveth</char>; surely they <char style="w" strong="H7650">swear</char> <char style="w" strong="H8267">falsely</char>. <verse eid="JER 5:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="JER 5:3" />O <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char>, <char style="add">are</char> not thine <char style="w" strong="H5869">eyes</char> upon the <char style="w" strong="H0530">truth</char>? thou hast <char style="w" strong="H5221">stricken</char> them, but they have not <char style="w" strong="H2342">grieved</char>; thou hast <char style="w" strong="H3615">consumed</char> them, <char style="add">but</char> they have <char style="w" strong="H3985">refused</char> to <char style="w" strong="H3947">receive</char> <char style="w" strong="H4148">correction</char>: they have made their <char style="w" strong="H6440">faces</char> <char style="w" strong="H2388">harder</char> than a <char style="w" strong="