>, and I have <char style="w" strong="H7971">sent</char> unto you, <char style="w" strong="H0559">saying</char>, Ye shall not <char style="w" strong="H0559">say</char>, The <char style="w" strong="H4853">burden</char> of the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char>; <verse eid="JER 23:38" /><verse number="39" style="v" sid="JER 23:39" />Therefore, behold, I, even I, will <char style="w" strong="H5377">utterly</char> <char style="w" strong="H5382">forget</char> you, and I will <char style="w" strong="H5203">forsake</char> you, and the <char style="w" strong="H5892">city</char> that I <char style="w" strong="H5414">gave</char> you and your <char style="w" strong="H0001">fathers</char>, <char style="add">and cast you</char> out of my <char style="w" strong="H6440">presence</char>: <verse eid="JER 23:39" /><verse number="40" style="v" sid="JER 23:40" />And I will <char style="w" strong="H5414">bring</char> an <char style="w" strong="H5769">everlasting</char> <char style="w" strong="H2781">reproach</char> upon you, and a <char style="w" strong="H5769">perpetual</char> <char style="w" strong="H3640">shame</char>, which shall not be <char style="w" strong="H7911">forgotten</char>.<verse eid="JER 23:40" /></para>
