    <verse number="8" style="v" sid="JER 24:8" />¶ And as the <char style="w" strong="H7451">evil</char> <char style="w" strong="H8384">figs</char>, which cannot be <char style="w" strong="H0398">eaten</char>, they are so <char style="w" strong="H7455">evil</char>; surely thus <char style="w" strong="H0559">saith</char> the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char>, So will I <char style="w" strong="H5414">give</char> <char style="w" strong="H6667">Zedekiah</char> the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3063">Judah</char>, and his <char style="w" strong="H8269">princes</char>, and the <char style="w" strong="H7611">residue</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3389">Jerusalem</char>, that <char style="w" strong="H7604">remain</char> in this <char style="w" strong="H0776">land</char>, and them that <char style="w" strong="H3427">dwell</char> in the <char style="w" strong="H0776">land</char> of <char style="w" strong="H4714">Egypt</char>: <verse eid="JER 24:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="JER 24:9" />And I will <char style="w" strong="H5414">deliver</char> them to be <char style="w" strong="H2189">removed</char> into all the <char style="w" strong="H4467">kingdoms</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H0776">earth</char> for <char style="add">their</char> <char style="w" strong="H7451">hurt</char>, <char style="add">to be</char> a <char style="w" strong="H2781">reproach</char> and a <char style="w" strong="H4912">proverb</char>, a <char style="w" strong="H8148">taunt</char> and a <char style="w" strong="H7045">curse</char>, in all <char style="w" strong="H4725">places</char> whither I shall <char style="w" strong="H5080">drive</char> them.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">24.9 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">to be removed: Heb. for removing, or, vexation</char></note> <verse eid="JER 24:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="JER 24:10" />And I will <char style="w" strong="H7