Achbor</char>, and <char style="add">certain</char> <char style="w" strong="H0582">men</char> with him into <char style="w" strong="H4714">Egypt</char>. <verse eid="JER 26:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="JER 26:23" />And they fetched <char style="w" strong="H3318">forth</char> <char style="w" strong="H0223">Urijah</char> out of <char style="w" strong="H4714">Egypt</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H0935">brought</char> him unto <char style="w" strong="H3079">Jehoiakim</char> the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char>; who <char style="w" strong="H5221">slew</char> him with the <char style="w" strong="H2719">sword</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H7993">cast</char> his dead <char style="w" strong="H5038">body</char> into the <char style="w" strong="H6913">graves</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H1121">common</char> <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">26.23 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">common…: Heb. sons of the people</char></note> <verse eid="JER 26:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="JER 26:24" />Nevertheless the <char style="w" strong="H3027">hand</char> of <char style="w" strong="H0296">Ahikam</char> the <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char> of <char style="w" strong="H8227">Shaphan</char> was with <char style="w" strong="H3414">Jeremiah</char>, that they should not <char style="w" strong="H5414">give</char> him into the <char style="w" strong="H3027">hand</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> to put him to <char style="w" strong="H4191">death</char>.<verse eid="JER 26:24" /></para>
