ys</char>, we, our <char style="w" strong="H0802">wives</char>, our <char style="w" strong="H1121">sons</char>, nor our <char style="w" strong="H1323">daughters</char>; <verse eid="JER 35:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="JER 35:9" />Nor to <char style="w" strong="H1129">build</char> <char style="w" strong="H1004">houses</char> for us to dwell <char style="w" strong="H3427">in</char>: neither have we <char style="w" strong="H3754">vineyard</char>, nor <char style="w" strong="H7704">field</char>, nor <char style="w" strong="H2233">seed</char>: <verse eid="JER 35:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="JER 35:10" />But we have dwelt <char style="w" strong="H3427">in</char> <char style="w" strong="H0168">tents</char>, and have <char style="w" strong="H8085">obeyed</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H6213">done</char> according to all that <char style="w" strong="H3122">Jonadab</char> our <char style="w" strong="H0001">father</char> <char style="w" strong="H6680">commanded</char> us. <verse eid="JER 35:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="JER 35:11" />But it came to pass, when <char style="w" strong="H5019">Nebuchadrezzar</char> <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> of <char style="w" strong="H0894">Babylon</char> came <char style="w" strong="H5927">up</char> into the <char style="w" strong="H0776">land</char>, that we <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char>, <char style="w" strong="H0935">Come</char>, and let us <char style="w" strong="H0935">go</char> to <char style="w" strong="H3389">Jerusalem</char> for <char style="w" strong="H6440">fear</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H2428">army</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H3778">Chaldeans</char>, and for <char style="w" strong="H6440">fear</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H2428">army</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H0758">Syrians</char>: so we <char style="w" strong="H3427">dwell</char> at <char style="w" strong="H3389">Jerusalem</char>.<verse eid="JER 35:11" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="12" style="v" sid="JER 35:12" />¶ Then came the <char style="w" strong="H1697">word</char> of the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> unto <char style="w" strong="H3414">Jeremiah</char>, <char style="w" strong="H0559">saying</char>, <verse eid="JER 35:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="JER 35:13" />Thus <char style="w" strong="H0559">saith</char> the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> of <char style="w" strong="H6635">hosts</char>, the <char style="w" strong="H0430">God</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>; <char style="w" strong="H1980">Go</char> and <char style="w" strong="H0559">tell</char> the <char style="w" strong="H0376">men</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3063">Judah</char> and the <char style="w" strong="H3427">inhabitants</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3389">Jerusalem</char>, Will ye not <char style="w" strong="H3947">receive</char> <char style="w" strong="H4148">instruction</char> to <char style="w" strong="H8085">hearken</char> to my <char style="w" strong="H1697">words</char>? <char style="w" strong="H5002">saith</char> the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char>. <verse eid="JER 35:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="JER 35:14" />The <char style="w" strong="H1697">words</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3082">Jonadab</char> the <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char> of <char style="w" strong="H7394">Rechab</char>, that he <char style="w" strong="H6680">commanded</char> his <char style="w" strong="H1121">sons</char> not to <char style="w" strong="H8354">drink</char> <char style="w" strong="H3196">wine</char>, are <char style="w" strong="H6965">performed</char>; for unto this <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char> they <char style="w" strong="H8354">drink</char> none, but <char style="w" strong="H8085">obey</char> their <char style="w" strong="H0001">father’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H4687">commandmen