ar style="w" strong="H0001">father</char>, which he <char style="w" strong="H6680">commanded</char> them; but this <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> hath not <char style="w" strong="H8085">hearkened</char> unto me: <verse eid="JER 35:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="JER 35:17" />Therefore thus <char style="w" strong="H0559">saith</char> the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> <char style="w" strong="H0430">God</char> of <char style="w" strong="H6635">hosts</char>, the <char style="w" strong="H0430">God</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>; Behold, I will <char style="w" strong="H0935">bring</char> upon <char style="w" strong="H3063">Judah</char> and upon all the <char style="w" strong="H3427">inhabitants</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3389">Jerusalem</char> all the <char style="w" strong="H7451">evil</char> that I have <char style="w" strong="H1696">pronounced</char> against them: because I have <char style="w" strong="H1696">spoken</char> unto them, but they have not <char style="w" strong="H8085">heard</char>; and I have <char style="w" strong="H7121">called</char> unto them, but they have not <char style="w" strong="H6030">answered</char>.<verse eid="JER 35:17" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="18" style="v" sid="JER 35:18" />¶ And <char style="w" strong="H3414">Jeremiah</char> <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char> unto the <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H7397">Rechabites</char>, Thus <char style="w" strong="H0559">saith</char> the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> of <char style="w" strong="H6635">hosts</char>, the <char style="w" strong="H0430">God</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>; Because ye have <char style="w" strong="H8085">obeyed</char> the <char style="w" strong="H4687">commandment</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3082">Jonadab</char> your <char style="w" strong="H0001">father</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H8104">kept</char> all his <char style="w" strong="H4687">precepts</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H6213">done</char> according unto all that he hath <char style="w" strong="H6680">commanded</char> you: <verse eid="JER 35:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="JER 35:19" />Therefore thus <char style="w" strong="H0559">saith</char> the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> of <char style="w" strong="H6635">hosts</char>, the <char style="w" strong="H0430">God</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>; <char style="w" strong="H3122">Jonadab</char> the <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char> of <char style="w" strong="H7394">Rechab</char> shall not <char style="w" strong="H3772">want</char> a <char style="w" strong="H0376">man</char> to <char style="w" strong="H5975">stand</char> <char style="w" strong="H6440">before</char> me for <char style="w" strong="H3117">ever</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">35.19 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Jonadab…: Heb. There shall not a man be cut off from Jonadab the son of Rechab to stand, etc</char></note><verse eid="JER 35:19" /></para>
